#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn13.11"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn13.11:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 13 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 13 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn13.11:0.2"
msgid "1. Abhisamayavagga "
msgstr "1. Comprehension "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn13.11:0.3"
msgid "11. Tatiyapabbatasutta "
msgstr "11. A Mountain (3rd) "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.139, sc1
msgctxt "sn13.11:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn13.11:1.2"
msgid "“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, puriso sinerussa pabbatarājassa satta muggamattiyo pāsāṇasakkharā upanikkhipeyya. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, suppose a person was to place down on Sineru, the king of mountains, seven pebbles the size of mung beans. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn13.11:1.3"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave, "
msgstr "What do you think, mendicants? "

msgctxt "sn13.11:1.4"
msgid "katamaṃ nu kho bahutaraṃ, yā vā satta muggamattiyo pāsāṇasakkharā upanikkhittā yo vā sineru pabbatarājā”ti? "
msgstr "Which is more: the seven pebbles the size of mung beans, or Sineru, the king of mountains?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn13.11:2.1"
msgid "“Etadeva, bhante, bahutaraṃ yadidaṃ sineru pabbatarājā; "
msgstr "“Sir, Sineru, the king of mountains, is certainly more. "

msgctxt "sn13.11:2.2"
msgid "appamattikā satta muggamattiyo pāsāṇasakkharā upanikkhittā. "
msgstr "The seven pebbles the size of mung beans are tiny. "

msgctxt "sn13.11:2.3"
msgid "Neva satimaṃ kalaṃ upenti na sahassimaṃ kalaṃ upenti na satasahassimaṃ kalaṃ upenti sineruṃ pabbatarājānaṃ upanidhāya satta muggamattiyo pāsāṇasakkharā upanikkhittā”ti. "
msgstr "Compared to Sineru, it’s not nearly a hundredth, a thousandth, or a hundred thousandth part.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn13.11:3.1"
msgid "“Evameva kho, bhikkhave, ariyasāvakassa diṭṭhisampannassa puggalassa adhigamaṃ upanidhāya aññatitthiyasamaṇabrāhmaṇaparibbājakānaṃ adhigamo neva satimaṃ kalaṃ upeti na sahassimaṃ kalaṃ upeti na satasahassimaṃ kalaṃ upeti. "
msgstr "“In the same way, compared with the achievements of a noble disciple accomplished in view, the achievements of the ascetics, brahmins, and wanderers who follow other paths is not nearly a hundredth, a thousandth, or a hundred thousandth part. "

msgctxt "sn13.11:3.2"
msgid "Evaṃ mahādhigamo, bhikkhave, diṭṭhisampanno puggalo, evaṃ mahābhiñño”ti. "
msgstr "So great is the achievement of the person accomplished in view, so great is their direct knowledge.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn13.11:3.3"
msgid "Ekādasamaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "sn13.11:3.4"
msgid "Abhisamayasaṃyuttaṃ samattaṃ. "
msgstr "The Linked Discourses on comprehension are complete. "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn13.11:4.1"
msgid "Nakhasikhā pokkharaṇī, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn13.11:4.2"
msgid "sambhejjaudake ca dve; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn13.11:4.3"
msgid "Dve pathavī dve samuddā, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn13.11:4.4"
msgid "tayo ca pabbatūpamāti. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
